  "title": "The List: A Traumady About Probiotic Masculinity",
  "description": "NOMINATED BEST STORYTELLING + BEST SCRIPT Montreal Fringe '24 Keith Serry's (PBS Stories From the Stage) hilarious and heartbreaking road trip from youth to old manhood is a search for guidance in a world where being “a good man” and being “the man” are two very different things. \"Delightful...moving.\" - Forget the Box MTL",
  "credits": "<strong>Playwright</strong>: Keith Serry<br/><strong>Director</strong>: David Crabb<br/><strong>Cast</strong>: Keith Serry<br/>",
  "website": "",
  "plain_language": "The List is a true story about how a boy named Keith grows into a man. As a lonely kid in a small town, Keith looks up to the wrong people and makes a list of what he thinks it means to be a man, but it’s all bad advice. In university, he meets Jenny, who likes him even though he’s unsure of himself. Scared of getting close, Keith tells her a lie outside a KFC. That lie forces him to rethink everything, including his role models, and helps him see the good influences that shaped who he really is.",
